cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the problem of inverse rendering, which is a topic in computer vision and graphics. The use of convolutional neural networks and differentiable rendering also suggests a focus on computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of multiview stereo, which is a technique commonly used in computer graphics and robotics, suggesting possible relevance to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of self-supervision and statistical priors also suggests possible relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
